http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Hyderabad/V.-Rama-Rao-laid-to-rest/article14006794.ece

The mortal remains of veteran Bharatiya Janata Party (BJP) leader and former Sikkim Governor V. Rama Rao were consigned to flames at ‘Mahaprasthanam’ in Whisper Valley here on Monday afternoon.Among those present during the last journey of the soft-spoken, much-loved leader were Union Minister M. Venkaiah Naidu, former Chief Minister K. Rosaiah, former Ministers Nagam Janardhan Reddy and S. Santosh Reddy and State Secretary S. Prakash Reddy. As the flames leapt into the air, they paid their respects.Earlier in the morning, Governor E.S.L. Narasimhan and Chief Minister K. Chandrasekhar Rao were among those who drove over to Rama Rao’s residence and paid their respects. Later, the body of Rama Rao was kept in the BJP’s State office for people to have a last glimpse, before the last journey began.Other leaders, who also came to the party office were Union Minister Nirmala Seetharaman, Suravaram Sudhakar Reddy, Chada Venkat Reddy, former MP Azeez Pasha and Manda Krishna Madiga, BJP’s national general secretary Muralidhar Rao, Union Minister Bandaru Dattatareya, Telangana State president and MLA G. Kishan Reddy, and the party’s floor leader in the State Assembly, K. Laxman.